{"word":"H8608 - תָּפַף - tâphaph - taw-faf' - Taber","slug":"H8608","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תָּפַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tâphaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>taw-faf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Taber"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05E4;&#x05E3; - ta&#x0302;phaph</b> - <i>taw-faf'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>drum</i>, that is, play (as) on the tambourine: - taber, play with timbrels."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8596\">H8596</a>"}]}